93","before 21 May 1393":"vóór 21 mei 1393","1390":"1390","Abt 1338":"circa 1338","Abt 1362":"circa 1362","1338":"1338","1335":"1335","1365":"1365","1321":"1321","about 1365":"circa 1365","before 16 October 1354":"vóór 16 oktober 1354","1319":"1319","1406":"1406","Laugharne, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Laugharne, Carmarthenshire, Wales","Okeford Fitzpaine, Dorset, England":"Okeford Fitzpaine, Dorset, England","Walwyn's Castle, Pembrokeshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Walwyn's Castle, Pembrokeshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1338–before 21 May 1393":"about 1338–before 21 May 1393","1335–1406":"1335–1406","1338–1393":"1338–1393","1321–1393":"1321–1393","1362–1394":"1362–1394","1365–1394":"1365–1394","1319–1390":"1319–1390","1295–Female":"1295–Deceased","before 1344":"before 1344","17 August 1390":"17 August 1390","1362":"1362","1295":"1295","1394":"1394","1393":"1393","before 21 May 1393":"before 21 May 1393","1390":"1390","Abt 1338":"about 1338","Abt 1362":"about 1362","1338":"1338","1335":"1335","1365":"1365","1321":"1321","about 1365":"about 1365","before 16 October 1354":"before 16 October 1354","1319":"1319","1406":"1406","Laugharne, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Laugharne, Carmarthenshire, Wales","Okeford Fitzpaine, Dorset, England":"Okeford Fitzpaine, Dorset, England","Walwyn's Castle, Pembrokeshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Walwyn's Castle, Pembrokeshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bryan","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Bryant  .","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of <b>Ó Briain</b>, see   O'Brien  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bryant","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the Celtic personal name <i>Brian</i> (from <i>brigo-</i> ‘high’ + the suffix <i>-ant-</i>), with excrescent <i>-t</i>. Breton bearers of this name were among the Normans who invaded England in 1066. They went on to settle in Ireland in the 12th century, where the name mingled with the native Irish form <i>Briain</i> (see   O'Brien  ). The latter had also been borrowed, as <i>Brján</i>, by the Vikings, who introduced it independently into northwestern England before the Norman Conquest.","Breton: very rare variant of   Briant   (see   Briand  ) and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this.","History: The American poet William Cullen Bryant (1794–1878) came of a New England family, being descended from Stephen Bryant, who had settled in Plymouth Colony in 1632."]},{"name":"Brine","meanings":["English (southern): from an early Middle English personal name <i>Brine</i> (Old English <i>Bryni</i>), a pet form of names in <i>Brūn</i> from <i>brūn</i> ‘brown’.","Welsh: possibly a variant of   Bryan   or   O'Brien   as a result of Irish immigration into southwest Wales, or a habitational name from the Pembrokes lordship of Dyffryn Breuan.","In some cases possibly also an Americanizedd form of German <b>Brein</b>, a variant of   Breun  ."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth Bryan was born about 1338, in Laugharne, Carmarthenshire, Wales, her father, Sir Guy Brienne, was 20 and her mother, Anne Holwey, was 45. She married Robert Fitzpayn before 16 October 1354. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died before 21 May 1393."},"et":{"Abt 1338–before 21 May 1393":"umbes 1338–enne 21. maid 1393","1335–1406":"1335–1406","1338–1393":"1338–1393","1321–1393":"1321–1393","1362–1394":"1362–1394","1365–1394":"1365–1394","1319–1390":"1319–1390","1295–Female":"1295–Surnud","before 1344":"enne 1344","17 August 1390":"17. august 1390","1362":"1362","1295":"1295","1394":"1394","1393":"1393","before 21 May 1393":"enne 21. maid 1393","1390":"1390","Abt 1338":"umbes 1338","Abt 1362":"umbes 1362","1338":"1338","1335":"1335","1365":"1365","1321":"1321","about 1365":"umbes 1365","before 16 October 1354":"enne 16. oktoobrit 1354","1319":"1319","1406":"1406","Laugharne, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Laugharne, Carmarthenshire, Wales","Okeford Fitzpaine, Dorset, England":"Okeford Fitzpaine, Dorset, England","Walwyn's Castle, Pembrokeshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Walwyn's Castle, Pembrokeshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1338–before 21 May 1393":"noin 1338–ennen vuotta 21. toukokuuta 1393","1335–1406":"1335–1406","1338–1393":"1338–1393","1321–1393":"1321–1393","1362–1394":"1362–1394","1365–1394":"1365–1394","1319–1390":"1319–1390","1295–Female":"1295–Kuollut","before 1344":"ennen vuotta 1344","17 August 1390":"17. elokuuta 1390","1362":"1362","1295":"1295","1394":"1394","1393":"1393","before 21 May 1393":"ennen vuotta 21. toukokuuta 1393","1390":"1390","Abt 1338":"noin 1338","Abt 1362":"noin 1362","1338":"1338","1335":"1335","1365":"1365","1321":"1321","about 1365":"noin 1365","before 16 October 